50|$|A {{cyclic order}} obeys a {{relatively}} strong 4-point transitivity axiom. One structure that weakens this axiom is a CC system: a <b>ternary</b> <b>relation</b> that is cyclic, asymmetric, and total, but generally not transitive. Instead, a CC system must obey a 5-point transitivity axiom {{and a new}} interiority axiom, which constrains the 4-point configurations that violate cyclic transitivity.|$|E
